   "source": [
    "## Case Study Lakes 3\n",
    "# Modelling Oxygen Dynamics in Lake Ägeri, Switzerland\n",
    "\n",
    "Biogeochemical Modelling of Lakes, Sediments and Oceans.\n",
    "\n",
    "Fabian Bärenbold, BMSLO, FS 2026\n",
    "\n",
    "In this project, you will develop a simple model for simulating oxygen concentrations in Lake Ägeri during the Fall and Winter season. During this period, the lake water at the surface cools down and the lake becomes stratified. As a result, the lake oxygen concentrations change over time and space.\n",
    "\n",
    "One of the most important drivers of oxygen concentration in lakes is photosynthetic oxygen production of phytoplankton. This oxygen production is hard to model because the phytoplankton community changes over time. In this project we therefore simplify the oxygen balance equation by neglecting photosynthesis.\n",
    "\n",
    "Our oxygen model is equivalent to what is presented in the seminal paper of Livingstone and Imboden (1996) except that we also investigate the effect of  the following processes:\n",
    "- vertical mixing between water layers (step 2)\n",
    "- gas exchange with the atmosphere (step 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "The model can be used to investigate the following questions:\n",
    "- Is oxygen consumption dominated by areal or volumetric consumption?\n",
    "- How sensitive is the model to prescribed mixing rates in the epilimnion, metalimnion and hypolimnion?\n",
    "- Is depth-independance a good assumption for oxygen consumption rates?\n",
    "\n",
    "The data used to build and validate the model is measured by an automatic measurement station in Lake Ägeri that measures depth profiles of temperature, conductivity, oxygen and algae pigments (https://www.eawag.ch/en/department/surf/projects/characterization-of-phytoplankton-and-lakes/).\n",
    "\n",
    "Study period: 01.11.2025 to 28.02.2026\n",
    "\n",
    "Governing equation: \n",
    "$$A(z)\\frac{\\partial O_2}{\\partial t}\n",
    "= \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial z} \\left(A(z) K(z) \\frac{\\partial O_2}{\\partial z} \\right)\n",
    "+ A(z)(J_v + J_a*\\alpha(z))$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where:\n",
    "\n",
    "- $z$ = vertical coordinate (depth)  \n",
    "- $t$ = time\n",
    "- $A(z)$ = depth-dependent lake cross-section  \n",
    "- $K(z)$ = vertical turbulent diffusivity  \n",
    "- $J_v$ = volumetric oxygen consumption rate (assumed to be constant with depth and time)  \n",
    "- $J_a$ = areal oxygen consumption rate (assumed to be constant with depth and time)  \n",
    "- $\\alpha(z)$ = ratio of sediment area to water volume at depth z as introduced by Livingstone and Imboden (1996)\n",
    "\n",
    "Assume gas exchange at the lake surface (at $z = 0$) as shown in the lecture.\n",
    "\n",
    "Model evaluation and comparison:\n",
    "- compare modeled and measured oxygen for several depth profiles (for example every 20 days)\n",
    "- compare modeled and measured oxygen concentrations for several fixed depths (for example at 10, 40 and 70 m depth)\n",
    "\n",
    "Available data:\n",
    "- lake morphology including surface area $A$ and sediment-to-water ratio $\\alpha$\n",
    "- mean daily mixing depth between 01.11.2025 and 28.02.2026\n",
    "- lake surface temperature between 01.11.2025 and 28.02.2026\n",
    "- dissolved oxygen concentration between 01.11.2025 and 28.02.2026, which can be used as initial conditions and for model evaluation\n"
   ]
  },
